annotationA: WASH complex subunit homolog 5; Acts at least in part as component of the WASH complex which may regulate wash nucleation-promoting factor (NPF) activity and is required for its membrane targeting during endosomal sorting (By similarity). During embryogenesis, not involved in the wash-dependent developmental migration of hemocytes anteriorly from the tail
